Load packages and set options

# load vector and raster packages
xfun::pkg_attach("ggplot2", "tidyr", "dplyr")

# options
options(tibble.width = 120, tibble.print_min = 15, pillar.min_title_chars = 15, dplyr.summarise.inform = FALSE)

# set working directory (for interactive console)
setwd("C:/DataProjects/fcbc")

Import data

Get data from Google sheet

# first get the column names
headers <- read.csv("https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vT_U2jN0hFq4aE6LP1e8Xn1_Oec6l_vngi18GR3ATR78HNR0jccePLg35IsX0Lp2eHrcCGm2zMHG0is/pub?gid=0&single=true&output=csv", header = FALSE, skip = 1, nrows = 1)

# then get the actual data and assign column names
data_csv <- read.csv("https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vT_U2jN0hFq4aE6LP1e8Xn1_Oec6l_vngi18GR3ATR78HNR0jccePLg35IsX0Lp2eHrcCGm2zMHG0is/pub?gid=0&single=true&output=csv", header = FALSE, skip = 3, col.names = headers)

# as tibble -- also useful for re-running code without https call
data <- as_tibble(data_csv)

# export for sharing
write.csv(data, "fcbc_sr_v1.csv")

Add UNSD info

Adds fields on UN region, etc.

# first need to separate out multiple countries
data <- data %>% separate_rows(location, sep = "(,\\s)")

# get unsd data
unsd <- read.csv("C:/DataProjects/fcbc/unsd_m49.csv")

# select data
unsd <- as_tibble(unsd) %>% select(Region.Code:Sub.region.Name, Country.or.Area, M49.Code, ISO.alpha3.Code, Developed...Developing.Countries)

# rename columns
unsd <- unsd %>% rename(country_name = Country.or.Area, region_code = Region.Code, region_name = Region.Name, subregion_code = Sub.region.Code, subregion_name = Sub.region.Name, country_m49 = M49.Code, country_iso3 = ISO.alpha3.Code, development_cat = Developed...Developing.Countries)

# join to data
data <- left_join(data, unsd, by = c("location" = "country_name"))

Restructure data

Move from wide to long table, consolidating columns which represent multiple values for a single record.

# inspect data and check variable types -- looks okay except for characters which should be factors
str(data)

# replace blanks with NA
data[data == ""] <- NA

# pivot longer for FWE type
data <- pivot_longer(data, starts_with("fwe_") & !ends_with("fwe_other"), names_to = "fwe_type", names_prefix = "(fwe_)", values_to = "fwe_log")
# pivot longer for FW use type
data <- pivot_longer(data, starts_with("use_") & !ends_with("use_other"), names_to = "use_type", names_prefix = "(use_)", values_to = "use_log")

# pivot longer for project action type
data <- pivot_longer(data, starts_with("act_") & !ends_with("act_other"), names_to = "action_type", names_prefix = "(act_)", values_to = "action_log")

# pivot longer for environmental outcome type
data <- pivot_longer(data, starts_with("eout_") & !starts_with("eout_other"), names_to = "enviroOutcome_type", names_prefix = "(eout_)", values_to = "enviroOutcome_effect")

# pivot longer for HWB outcome type
data <- pivot_longer(data, starts_with("hout_") & !starts_with("hout_other"), names_to = "hwbOutcome_type", names_prefix = "(hout_)", values_to = "hwbOutcome_effect")

# reorder columns
data <- data %>% relocate(id:location, fwe_type, fwe_log, fwe_other, use_type, use_log, use_other, action_type, action_log, act_other, enviroOutcome_type:hwbOutcome_effect)

# rename columns with non-verbose names
data <- data %>% rename(enviroOutcome_other = eout_other, enviroOutcome_other_effect = eout_other_effect, hwbOutcome_other = hout_other, hwbOutcome_other_effect = hout_other_effect, action_other = act_other)

# inspect revised data
str(data)
